disease_name: Rett syndrome (particularly atypical forms which predominantly affect males)
Angelman syndrome (though typically intellectual disability is present, there are mosaic or milder variants)
PTEN Hamartoma Tumor syndrome (includes conditions such as Cowden syndrome)
SYNGAP1-related intellectual disability (though often includes intellectual disability, there can be milder cases)
KIAA2022-related intellectual disability (though intellectual disability is common, some cases might present with autism without intellectual disability)

Please note that the exclusion of intellectual disability and seizures shall typically narrow the diagnosis to conditions primarily associated with autism alone, but milder and atypical presentations of other syndromes can still be considered.
